# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kravn — TIER-1 (bootstrap) configuration ONLY.
# Everything else is configured at RUNTIME from the admin UI (stored in the DB).
# Kravn boots with ZERO of these set: SQLite file + an auto-generated key.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# HTTP port (default: 8080)
# PORT=8080

# Where to store data when using the default embedded SQLite DB (default: ./data)
# KRAVN_DATA_DIR=./data

# Database connection. The schema is built and migrated automatically on boot for any of these.
#   - Unset      -> embedded SQLite at ${KRAVN_DATA_DIR}/kravn.sqlite (zero setup)
#   - SQLite     -> sqlite:///absolute/or/relative/path.sqlite
#   - PostgreSQL -> postgres://user:pass@host:5432/db?sslmode=require   (Azure Postgres: keep sslmode=require)
#   - MySQL      -> mysql://user:pass@host:3306/db   (MariaDB: mariadb://...)
#   - SQL Server -> sqlserver://user:pass@host:1433/db?encrypt=true
# Must end with the database name (/db). SQLAlchemy "+driver" forms (e.g. postgresql+psycopg://) are
# accepted and normalized. An unknown scheme fails fast with a clear message (it is NOT treated as a file).
# DATABASE_URL=

# Build all tables inside a specific DB schema (PostgreSQL + SQL Server). Empty -> the default schema.
# The schema is auto-created if missing. Must be a simple identifier.
#   - PostgreSQL: applied via searchPath (default schema is "public").
#   - SQL Server: applied by repointing the login's DEFAULT_SCHEMA. Use a NON-sysadmin login
#     (Kravn repoints it for you); a sysadmin login like "sa" always maps to dbo and the schema is
#     ignored with a warning (tables go to dbo, consistently).
#   - SQLite: N/A. MySQL: the "schema" is the database — set it in DATABASE_URL.
# KRAVN_DB_SCHEMA=

# Secret used to sign JWTs and encrypt stored credentials.
#   - Unset in single-node -> auto-generated once and persisted to ${KRAVN_DATA_DIR}/secret.key
#   - REQUIRED (32+ chars) when running multiple replicas so they share one key.
# KRAVN_SECRET=

# Public URL (used for OAuth callbacks / absolute links).
#   - Unset -> auto-derived from the incoming request (Host / X-Forwarded-*).
# KRAVN_PUBLIC_URL=

# Which slice of the backend this process serves (same image, different pods):
#   all (default) | gateway (control-plane API + MCP + operator UI) | chat (end-user chat API only)
# KRAVN_ROLE=all

# Base URL of the separate end-user client SPA. Required for SSO "sign in" from the client app
# (the gateway redirects the token here when login starts with returnTo=client). e.g. https://chat.example.com
# In local dev with the client on Vite: KRAVN_CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5174
# KRAVN_CLIENT_URL=

# Optional: bootstrap the first admin without the setup wizard.
# If unset, the first run serves a setup wizard in the UI instead.
# KRAVN_ADMIN_EMAIL=
# KRAVN_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# NODE_ENV=production
